Adjust rack to upper position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve @zucchini{2} lengthwise, then slice into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Zest and halve @lemon{1}. Peel @Yukon Gold potatoes{24%oz}, then cut into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallots{2}. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}.

Toss zucchini with lemon zest, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} on a #baking sheet{}. Place lemon halves on sheet beside zucchini. Roast, flipping halfway through, until tender and browned, about ~{10%minutes}. Set aside, covered.

Meanwhile, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 1 inch. Cover and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Cook until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Scoop out and reserve ¼ cup cooking water, then drain.

Return empty pot to stove over low heat and add @butter{2%tbsp}. Once melted, return potatoes to pot; mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Stir in @cream cheese{8%tbsp} and @sour cream{4%tbsp}. Add enough cooking water to create a creamy consistency (you may not use all). Season with plenty of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Set aside, covered to keep warm.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @chicken cutlets{20%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}.

Add chicken to pan and cook until no longer pink in center, ~{2-4%minutes} per side. Set aside on a #plate{}, covered.

Add @butter{2%tbsp} and shallots to same pan over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until shallots soften slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2} and ¼ cup water, scraping up any browned bits on bottom. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer until thick and saucy, ~{2-4%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Reduce heat under pan to low and stir in any juices released by chicken. Top zucchini with as much juice from roasted lemon as you'd like; toss to coat. Divide chicken, potatoes, and zucchini between plates. Top chicken with sauce. Garnish with scallions and serve.